SIMPLE: counterterm
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Counterterm
<hw>Coun"ter*term`</hw> <pr>(-t?rm`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A term or
word which is the opposite of, or antithesis to, another; an antonym; --
the opposite of <xex>synonym</xex>; <as>as, ⟦ldquo⟧foe⟦rdquo⟧ is the
<ex>counterterm</ex> of ⟦ldquo⟧friend⟦rdquo⟧</as>.</def> <rj><au>C. J.
Smith.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Countertime</ent>⟦br⟧
